      • selfDestruct

        public User selfDestruct()
        The function selfDestruct() removes a user from the environment. Since the user ID may still be referenced somewhere, the user is not hard deleted from the database, instead the account is set inactive and invisible.

        To allow recreation of an account with the same login the login is cleaned - otherwise it would be blocked eternally by the login existence test performed in the BenutzerverwaltungForm.Speichern() function. In addition, all personally identifiable information is removed from the database as well.
